---
title: Chicken and Bacon Yakisoba-Style Noodles with Gai Lan and Mixed Mushrooms
description: Whip up some yakisoba tonight! These Japanese-inspired noodles are stir-fried with smoky bacon, tender gai lan and savoury mixed mushrooms, all cloaked in a savoury stir-fry sauce. Top it all off with some golden chicken bites!

Ingredients: Chicken breast • Ramen noodles (wheat flour, water, potassium carbonate, food color (yellow #5), potassium sorbate) (wheat) • Mushroom mix (cremini mushrooms, white mushrooms, oyster mushrooms) • Gai lan • Carrots • Bacon (pork, water, salt, sugar, sodium phosphates, sodium erythorbate, sodium nitrite, spices, smoke) • Soy sauce-mirin blend (salted mirin (glucose, fermented rice extract, water, salt), water, soy sauce (soybean, maltodextrin, salt), salt, natural flavour (autolyzed yeast), citric acid, potassium sorbate, sodium benzoate) (soy) • Hoisin sauce (sugars (sugar, glucose, fancy molasses), water, tomato paste, soy sauce (soybean, maltodextrin, salt) vinegar, modified corn starch, rice vinegar, tahini (sesame), salt, soybean oil, sesame oil, mustard, garlic powder, onion powder, spices, natural flavour, xanthan gum, citric acid, caramel, potassium sorbate, sodium benzoate) (soy, sesame, mustard) • Green onion • Ginger garlic puree (garlic, water, ginger, soybean oil, spices, citric acid, xanthan gum, potassium sorbate) • Cream sauce spice blend (wheat flour, salt, garlic powder, onion powder, canola oil, silicon dioxide) (wheat) • Sesame seeds.
